## Mission
Turn our ARKEM Figma system into a React + Storybook library using ONLY tokens (no raw values). Components mirror Figma variants/sizes/states, are accessible, and ship with well-documented stories.

## Tech
- React 18, TypeScript strict
- Storybook (Vite)
- Tokens as CSS variables
- Icons: lucide-react
- Optional: Tailwind (design authoring only)

## Folders
src/
  styles/                 # tokens.css + tokens-semantic.css
  components/             # <Name>/<Name>.tsx + <Name>.stories.tsx
  kepler/                 # Kepler shells & stories (mocked)
.storybook/

## Ground Rules
1) Never hardcode visual values. Use variables from:
   - /src/styles/tokens.css
   - /src/styles/tokens-semantic.css
2) Each component:
   - lives in `src/components/<Name>/`
   - has typed props mapped to Figma variants
   - includes focus-visible and ARIA
   - ships `*.stories.tsx` with Controls for all props
3) Storybook:
   - `title: "Components/<Name>"`
   - layout centered unless the pattern needs full width
4) New visuals â†’ propose a semantic token and add it to tokens-semantic.css, then refactor usage.

